race.comment: PRIVALOVA (13) improved second up beaten 3.5 lengths over 1210m at Kilmore and is still well shy of her best. Has her share of ability and will be hard to beat in a suitable race. MACHA (12) is another with improvement to come. Led unexpectedly at Benalla second-up over a mile and is back is grade and distance. Fitter again and can get into the finish. FROZEN TIDE (4) resumes in easier company and his jumpouts have been sharp. He's likely to return further improved and will get every chance from an inside gate. ELLE MCFEARSOME (11) just missed at Gunbower first-up over 1300m and is back on track. Has an awkward gate but is proven second-up and can't be ruled out.
